Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, out Stoinis Run Out!! 1 run completed. Oh no! Stoinis is furious at Dhawan. This is a big moment in this game. The in-form Stoinis has been sent back with just over three overs remaining. Tossed up delivery and Stoinis drags it off the inner half towards long-on, they were settling with the single but Suryakumar fumbles and that prompts Stoinis to turn for the second, Dhawan does not respond and he is left stranded a long way out of the crease. Dhawan was late in sending him back and that's what resulted in Stoinis fuming off. Stoinis run out (Suryakumar Yadav/Rahul Chahar) 13(8) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Ashwin to de Kock, out Caught by Prithvi Shaw!! The partnership is broken and Ashwin is pumped up. Much-needed breakthrough for Delhi. A tossed up delivery that drifts in on leg at 84kph, de Kock shapes up to slog-sweep and is done in by the dip. Only manages a top edge and holes out at deep backward square leg. Shaw holds onto it safely. QdK is distraught as he walks off the field. Can Delhi make further inroads? de Kock c Prithvi Shaw b Ashwin 53(36) [4s-4 6s-3]
